  "title": "Technical Engineer (Electrical - Open to fresh graduates)",
  "description": "<h3><strong>Company Overview</strong></h3><p>Our client is an international company specializing in asset management solutions for electrical infrastructure and power network operators. They support utilities, infrastructure owners, and energy companies across Southeast Asia by enhancing the reliability, safety, and performance of critical electrical assets. Leveraging strong engineering expertise, data-driven tools, and consulting capabilities, the company helps clients optimize maintenance strategies, extend asset lifespan, and reduce operational costs.<br /></p><h3><strong>Job Responsibilities</strong></h3><ul><li>Provide technical solutions and advisory support to customers</li><li>Conduct product training and deliver high-quality technical support</li><li>Work closely with customers to understand requirements and recommend appropriate solutions</li><li>Travel within Southeast Asia to meet customers and support projects as required</li></ul><h3>The ideal candidate should possess:</h3><ul><li>Degree in Electrical Engineering or equivalent (fresh graduates are welcome to apply)</li><li>Knowledge of electrical assets, the electricity industry, and relevant regulations is an advantage</li><li>Strong interpersonal, communication, time management, and problem-solving skills</li><li>Possession of a Class 3 driving license</li></ul>",
